description.narrative: (Tanzania): With FY 2020 funding, the Boresha Afya Lake/Western activity will increase access to integrated comprehensive and high-quality, facility-based health services to meet malaria and MNCH needs in seven regions of the Lake and Western zones (Geita, Kagera, Kigoma, Mara, Mwanza, Simiyu, and Shinyanga) and Zanzibar. This activity will seek innovative ways to empower communities to advocate for needs and increase access to facilities. Additionally, the activity will facilitate joint planning and implementation with selected facilities and Council HMTs, and assist Regional HMTs with data review and quality assurance. The activity will help lead the development of national policy for MNCH and malaria on the Mainland and provide support to Zanzibar. This activity will contribute to the U.S. government's objective of improving the health status of Tanzanians and the PMI. The activity will provide technical assistance to improve MNCH and malaria service delivery through capacity building of health care providers; mentoring and supportive supervision; strengthened referral systems with enhanced networks of care and support; and community engagement which includes advocacy and outreach services. The activity will procure equipment for health facilities.... .
